SUBREDDIT: r/weddingplanning

TITLE: A timeline issue... What to do?

POST: My fiancé and I are getting married on December 29th at 6:30pm. We were looking into where to do our photos and found a cute little 1911 mansion turned museum that was charging a reasonable rate. So, I emailed our photographer to ask his opinion. This was last week Thursday, and I have yet to hear back from him. We were waiting to sign the contract with the museum and put down the deposit until we got his opinion.

On Monday, we get an email from the coordinator at the museum stating that they had a couple who needed to move their wedding to our date, and so the museum would no longer be available at the time we had requested (4-5:30). She also generously offered us use of the museum at no charge if we were out of there by 4:00.

Like I said, our ceremony starts at 6:30, with guests beginning to arrive at 6. So, that would leave us with 2 hours with nothing to do, and it also cuts into our time with our photographer, potentially jeopardizing photos of our exit from the reception at the end of the night.

The museum is really the kind of setting we were looking for--classic architecture, vintage furnishings and decor--and the price is certainly right.

What do you think?
